Have you ever #lived in a #flat or a #house that #nolongerexists in #Singapore? 
Please PM with your #name and your full ex-address if you wish to be a part of a new work that I am #thinking of #making. 
The work is quite #simple; it will be your name and ex-address plainly typed out (in #TimesNewRoman) and #printed on a #surface (I haven't decided which surface yet!) that is the size of a #letter sized #envelope. This will hang next to all the other names and ex-#address in a #grid like form in a #gallery #space. 
Thank you! Please freely #forward this and let #everyone who has such an #experience in Singapore that you know who might want to be a #part of this. #HemanChong #Art #NewWork #EnBloc #hdbflats #Condo #Landed #UltraMansion

Will Ferrell delivered the commencement address to the University of Southern California's graduating class of 2017. As a USC alumnus, he told the audience that he once began as an intern with NBC Sports, only to realize that comedy was his true path. He shared stories of personal memories as a college student, as well as some of his great life moments of success. "You’re never not afraid. I’m still afraid,” he said. “My fear of failure never approached in magnitude my fear of "What if? What if I never tried at all?"
